  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Animal studies showed that controlled mechanical ventilation (CMV) can induce dysfunction of
      the diaphragm, resulting in an early-onset and progressive decrease in diaphragmatic
      force-generating capacity, called ventilator-induced diaphragmatic dysfunction (VIDD).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
